  "prompt": "What can I do if my new CA driver's license hasn't come in the mail?",
  "response": "If your new California driver's license hasn't arrived in the mail, here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Wait at least 3-4 weeks after applying/renewing before taking action.\n\n2. Check your temporary paper license: This document is typically valid for 60 days and serves as proof of your driving privileges.\n\n3. Contact the DMV:\n- Call their customer service line at 1-800-777-0133\n- Check online at dmv.ca.gov for status\n- Use the DMV online license lookup tool\n\n4. Visit a local DMV office in person to inquire about the status of your license\n\n5. Verify your mailing address: Make sure the address on file is correct\n\n6. Request a replacement license if it's been more than 60 days:\n- You can do this online\n- Visit a DMV office\n- Pay a replacement fee (around $35)\n\nRemember to bring:\n- Proof of identity\n- Proof of residency\n- Your temporary paper license\n- Payment for replacement fee\n\nIf you're experiencing ongoing issues, consider visiting a DMV office in person for direct assistance.",
